 464:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** 
 465:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** /*********************************************************************
 466:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *
 467:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *       SEGGER_RTT_printf
 468:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *
 469:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *  Function description
 470:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    Stores a formatted string in SEGGER RTT control block.
 471:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    This data is read by the host.
 472:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *
 473:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *  Parameters
 474:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    BufferIndex  Index of "Up"-buffer to be used. (e.g. 0 for "Terminal")
 475:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    sFormat      Pointer to format string, followed by the arguments for conversion
 476:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *
 477:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *  Return values
 478:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    >= 0:  Number of bytes which have been stored in the "Up"-buffer.
 479:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *     < 0:  Error
 480:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *
 481:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *  Notes
 482:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    (1) Conversion specifications have following syntax:
 483:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          %[flags][FieldWidth][.Precision]ConversionSpecifier
 484:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *    (2) Supported flags:
 485:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          -: Left justify within the field width
 486:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          +: Always print sign extension for signed conversions
 487:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          0: Pad with 0 instead of spaces. Ignored when using '-'-flag or precision
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Administrator\AppData\Local\Temp\ccMWu2fp.s 			page 32


 488:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *        Supported conversion specifiers:
 489:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          c: Print the argument as one char
 490:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          d: Print the argument as a signed integer
 491:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          u: Print the argument as an unsigned integer
 492:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          x: Print the argument as an hexadecimal integer
 493:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          s: Print the string pointed to by the argument
 494:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** *          p: Print the argument as an 8-digit hexadecimal integer. (Argument shall be a pointer to
 495:Middlewares/Third_Party/SEGGER/RTT/SEGGER_RTT_printf.c **** */
